===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# {{lb|zh|historical}} [[crack]]s formed on heated [[tortoise]] [[plastron]]s and mammal bones used in ancient [[divination]]
#* {{zh-x|是 月 也，命 大{tài}史 釁 龜-策，占{zhān}-兆 審-卦 吉凶。|In this month orders are given to the Grand Scribe to smear with blood the tortoise-shells and divining stalks, and by interpreting the '''indications''' of the former and examining the figures formed by the latter, to determine the good and evil of their intimations.|ref=Liji-L}}
#* {{zh-x|是以 不 擇 時日，不 占{zhān} 卦-兆，不 謀 所-始，不 議 所-終。|That being so, there was no selecting of [auspicious] times and days, no divining by trigrams or '''shell cracks''', no scheming about where to begin, no discussion of where to end.|ref=Huainanzi}}
# [[omen]]
#: {{zh-x|吉兆|auspicious omen}}
#* {{zh-x|相 陰陽，占{zhān} 祲-兆，鑽 龜 陳 卦，主 攘擇 五-卜，知 其 吉凶 妖-祥，傴-巫 跛-擊 之 事 也。|The work of the hunchbacked shamans and lame-footed seers is to assess the yin and the yang, to divine the omens and '''portents''', to drill the tortoise-shells and lay out the hexagrams, to preside over ceremonies for warding off ills, selecting lucky days, and the five prognostications, and to know good and bad fortune, the auspicious and the inauspicious.|ref=Xunzi}}
# to [[portend]]; to [[augur]]
# [[graveyard]], [[cemetery]], [[necropolis]]
#* {{zh-x|吾 力 能 改葬，終 葬 汝 於 先人 之 兆，然後 惟其 所-願。|If I could rebury, I would rebury you in our ancestors' '''graveyard'''; only then would it be satisfactory.|CL-L|ref={{lang|zh|{{lw|zh|韓愈}}}} {{w|Han Yu}} {{lang|zh|《{{lw|zh|s:祭十二郎文|祭十二郎文}}》}} "Funeral Oration for my Twelfth Nephew", 803 CE.}}
# {{lb|zh|chiefly|Taiwan}} [[trillion]] (million million), [[tera-]], 10<sup>12</sup>
# {{lb|zh|Mainland China|Hong Kong}} ([[International System of Units|SI]] prefix) [[million]], [[mega-]], 10<sup>6</sup>
#* {{zh-x|專 惟 君 而 無 他 兮，又 眾兆 之 所-讎。|I thought of my prince alone, and of no other; and that, too, was a thing that the mob of '''hundreds of myriads''' abhorred.|ref=Chuci-H}}

